the emirates " al-bayan " newspaper published today , saturday , quotes the study , which was prepared by the gulf industrial consultancy organization , as saying that the gulf area is witnessing rapid development in communication and information technology and that most indicators point to the success of the establishment of this type of industry in the area given that the gulf area , with the capacities it possesses , is likely to become an important international centre for the information technology industry .
the study , entitled " horizons for establishing an information technology industry in the cooperation council states and impact on diversification of exports " , says that there is a pressing need for an integrated information technology industry in the gulf area , where the gulf states still rely on and meet their needs by employing workers from the neighboring arab states and from other asian states , such as india and the philippines . for this reason , it is necessary to continue monitoring the development of the communication and information technology infrastructure . "
additional foreign investments after riyadh bombings .
riyadh 3 january ( xinhua ) a recent economic report says that the terrorist bombings experienced by riyadh have had no effect on foreign investments in saudi arabia .
the report , which was published by the daily " al-iqtisadiyah " newspaper here today , says that in the month of last june , which followed the riyadh bombings ( may ) , the value of foreign investments that were licensed exceeded 222 million saudi riyals ( american dollar equals 3.75 saudi riyals ) , a figure that exceeds the average monthly total for investment in the first half of 2003 .
the report issued by the saudi british bank , expects the value of foreign investments to rise during the present year , 2004 , because the saudi government is proceeding to adopt all the policies that should attract more foreign investments .
the report adds that the evidence shows that foreign companies are usually attracted by investment incentives , the ability to return profits , the level of economic growth and positive government policies generally towards foreign investments , which factor appears to be currently present in the saudi investment market .
official : angolan economy looks promising for 2004 .
luanda 3 january ( xinhua ) a banking official in angola said that the economic forecast for his country in 2004 looked promising and that " the goal is to continue working towards the realization of stability in his country 's economy " .
local media quoted amado maricio , governor of the angolan national bank , as saying today , saturday , that angola 's gross national product will continue to grow rapidly and that the country 's oil production will see a similar increase .
according to the governor , the establishment and improvement of a financial market governed by clear and objective rules and regulations will help to improve investment efficiency and encourage an increase in the saving rates of citizens .
he added that banking and non - banking operations aiming to establish financial monitoring structures in accordance with the aims of realizing market stability are still on going to date .
however , mauricio said that the priority would be given to those investing for the medium and long term , in particular major institutional investors , investment promoters , loan cooperatives and small loan associations .
he said that one of the priorities of the angolan national bank was to give incentives to create other sources of funding for small economic activities with consumption to be controlled by rules .
khaddam reiterates his country 's stance alongside iraq .
damascus 3 january ( xinhua ) syrian vice president abd al-halim khaddam reiterated the stance of his country alongside iraq in the construction of its independent state over all its national territory whilst receiving a delegation from iraqi tribes headed by muhammad tahir today , saturday .
khaddam stressed the importance of national unity and iraqi national concord in order to confront the tribulation through which iraq is passing at this stage , according to the syrian arab news agency .
khaddam confirmed that the iraqi people alone have the right to determine their future , build their state and future and administer the affairs of their country by means of elections conducted under united nations supervision . he drew attention to the fact that any weakness in the national unity process could have dangerous and harmful consequences for all iraqi brothers in all their groups and sects .
abd al-halim khaddam gave a statement to journalists following the meeting in which he confirmed that syria was working hard to provide all the assistance that could be provided to the iraqi people to lighten the difficulties they suffer . he expressed hope that iraqis would be able to realize their national aspirations soon .
the iraqi delegation arrived in damascus yesterday evening , friday , in a two - day visit to syria during which the delegation will hold talks with senior syrian officials .
three american soldiers wounded in explosives attack in northern iraq .
baghdad 4 january ( xinhua ) the american army announced this evening , sunday , that three american soldiers were wounded following an explosives attack against them in northern iraq .
cnn , the american news network , quoting sources in the american forces , reported that the attack took place near the village of bija in northern iraq whilst a convoy of occupation forces was on a routine security mission to accompany a group of american government contractors .
meanwhile , it added that the american government had denied reports that american soldiers had violated islamic sunni rites in iraq when storming the mosque of ibn taimiyyah in baghdad .
sheikh abd al-sattar al-janabi , deputy secretary general of the supreme propagation , guidance and fatwa authority in iraq had accused the american forces of plundering accounts , cameras and donation boxes at the ibn taimiyyah mosque , formerly umm al-tubul , the day before yesterday , friday .
syrian president visits turkey in first visit of its kind in 57 years .
ankara 5 january ( xinhua ) syrian president bashar al-asad is expected to visit turkey on tuesday in a visit that is the first of its kind in 57 years .
this was mentioned by the turkish presidential press office in a statement today , monday .
during the official three - day visit , al-asad will discuss with his turkish counterpart ahmet necdet sezer bilateral relations and the iraq issue .
diplomatic sources reported that the documents preventing dual taxation between turkey and syria , joint encouragement and protection of investments and the sixth tourism protocol would be signed during the visit .
al-asad , it has been decided , will meet with turkish parliamentary speaker bulent ajawid and prime minister recep tayyip erdogan , foreign minister and deputy prime minister abdullah gul , leader of the people 's republican party diniz baykal 's and chief of the general staff general hilmi ozkok .
he is also expected to meet with syrian nationals living in istanbul and turkish businessmen .
sales revenues in chinese village
nanjing 6 january ( xinhua ) reports from the village of hawashi to the city of jiangin in the province of jiangshu , eastern china , mention that this very famous village in china has achieved more than 10 billion yuan ( about 1.2 billion american dollars ) from sales revenues in 2003 , an increase of 59% on 2002 .
hawashi village generated 100 million yuan ( about 12 million american dollars ) for the first time from revenue in 1980 .
the village held a meeting to discuss its business last year on the 2nd of this january , in which liang paw hua , governor of the province of jiangshu , praised the village of hawashi as being a model of rural development in china .
hawashi has about 8 companies comprising 58 firms , which use a cooperative system , a system of oversight by members of the board of directors , a system for the responsibility of the director and a system for debate via a conference of workers and staff representatives .
official : surrender of 600 rebels to ugandan government .
kampala 6 january ( xinhua ) the ugandan government is negotiating with the united nations mission in the democratic republic of congo regarding the surrender of more than 600 fighters from the allied democratic forces , according to the ugandan amnesty committee .
the local monitor newspaper today quoted the chairman of the committee janiana miro as saying , " we are in the last stages of talks with rebels with the help of the united nations mission in democratic congo and an agreement will be reached soon . "
the committee received more than 400 former rebels who belong to a group from the west nile front under the command of taban amin son of late leader idi amin .
miro said , " we always knew that the rebels of the allied democratic forces were 500 , but the number is a little more than this . "
elsewhere , about 22 front rebels were released from the kijo prison last month after they had been detained for more than one year .
the front declared war on the government in 1996 but was defeated in 2000 .
american administration awards contracts to equip commercial aircraft with anti - missile systems .
washington 6 january ( xinhua ) the american department of homeland security announced on tuesday that it had selected bae systems , northrop grumman and united airlines to develop plans to provide security protection for american commercial aircraft to protect them from shoulder - borne missiles .
charles mcqueary , under secretary for science and technology at the department of homeland security , explained that under the agreement the three companies would work on a plan to equip commercial aircraft with military missiles detection systems and counter - measures .
each company will receive two million us dollars for the first stage of the project , which will run for six months .
mcqueary added that subsequently one or two contractors will be chosen to conduct more precise tests for a period extending more than 18 months .
mcqueary noted that the three companies had been selected from among 24 nominated companies that had submitted bids in response to the tender put out last october .
israeli legislator confirms secret contacts with libya .
jerusalem 7 january ( xinhua ) ephraim sneh , a member of the labor party in the israeli knesset ( parliament ) , today confirmed a report stating that he had conducted secret contacts with libya .
sneh told radio israel that he and legislator ilan shalgi from the shinui party met with the son of libyan president muammar gaddafi in august of last year .
sneh said of the libyan leader , " my impression from my meeting was that gaddafi had taken a strategic decision and that he was not a man of small steps . "
he will not stop halfway .
he could go on to establish relations with israel and more than that . "
" my impression from my conversation with gaddafi 's son , who is said to be his heir , is that they had begun a tour of the world to study this modern world that they wish to join . "
sneh 's statements came as the israeli foreign ministry began a diplomatic initiative to develop relations with libya .
ten days earlier ron prosor , israeli foreign ministry official , left for paris to meet with an arab official and discuss the possibility of establishing relations with tripoli .
libya surprised the world recently by announcing its readiness to get rid of weapons of mass destruction and join the international community on the basis of improving relations with the united states , britain and france .
sri lanka 's prime minister urges president to undertake peace mission to tamil rebels .
colombo 7 january ( xinhua ) sri lanka 's prime minister ranil wickremesinghe urged his political rival president chandrika kumaratunga to undertake a peace mission with the tamil rebels .
before an assembly in the village of bandoasnwara in the northeast , wickremesinghe said that it was the responsibility of president kumaratunga to undertake a peace mission with the rebels of the tamil tigers front to liberate the people of ailam in the same way that she took responsibility for three key ministries in the government on the 4th of november last year .
he said , " the measure she took to take responsibility for the three ministries by herself requires that she undertake the peace process . "
kumaratunga took the defense , interior and media ministries from the grasp of wickremesinghe on the 4th of november last year , sending the country into political crisis .
wickremesinghe said that for his part he was unable to continue the peace process with norwegian mediation without controlling the ministry of defense .
he explained , " the peace process depends on the ceasefire .
we signed an agreement for a ceasefire with the front on the basis that we had full powers as a government .
but the president 's actions threaten this basis . "
china on state of maximum alert for possible spread of sars at height of travel season .
( first and final addition ) .
the ministry of railways urged all train stations to continue the state of alert against sars and to inspect the temperature of every passenger .
in peking train station , which deals with about 100 thousand passengers every day at the height of the season , passengers are dealt with in a systematic way after their temperatures are examined .
a spokesman for the station said , " we have strengthened the daily waste and ventilation activities in every part of the station . in addition , we are examining the temperature of passengers , as well as that of station staff before they begin their work . "
in the kuangdong province the local railways authorities resumed 24 hour working on a daily basis with effect from 30 december 2003 and established a system for notification and control to examine any potential health emergency .
the local marine and marine transport sectors are asking every passenger with a high temperature to undergo a medical examination .
the world health organization has greatly praised the system of monitoring and control in china against sars and said that there was no need at the present time to request the chinese government to change the schedule for the peak travel season
uraiqat holds israel responsible for military escalation in palestinian territories .
gaza 8 january ( xinhua ) palestinian minister of negotiations saib uraiqat said today , thursday , that the israeli government was responsible for the results and consequences of the military escalation in the palestinian territories .
uraiqat said that he had conducted a series of contacts with a number of states , especially with the american and european sides , to urge them to intervene to halt the israeli attacks , assassinations and raids and to send international monitors and force israel to implement the road map .
uraiqat called on the american administration to activate the role of the international group of four committee and bear its responsibilities for driving forward the peace process . he stressed " the urgency of providing implementation mechanisms , schedules and international monitoring on the ground for the full implementation of the road map " .
he explained that the israeli government had taken no steps to bring about progress in the peace process between the two sides . it was persisting in its closure of palestinian offices and institutions in jerusalem , continuing its detention of prisoners and detainees and had not withdrawn to the point it was at before 28 september 2000 , which represents part of the obligations incumbent on the israeli government in the first stage of the " road map " , which provides for the establishment of the palestinian state by the start of 2005 .
norway closes cairo embassy because of unspecific threat ( expanded ) .
cairo 8 january ( xinhua ) norwegian diplomatic sources here said today , thursday , that their country had decided to close its embassy in cairo until next sunday to counter threats directed at the diplomatic mission in egypt .
the same sources told the xinhua correspondent that the decision came as part of an evaluation of the level of threat confronting norway from extremist islamic organizations , at the forefront of which stands the al-qaeda organization .
the xinhua correspondent also had contacts with officials in the egyptian ministry of the interior and learnt that no statement had yet been issued by the egyptian authorities on this matter .
the al-qaeda organization had included norway on the list of states it called to be confronted in may 2003 when ayman al-zawahiri ( egyptian national ) , the right - hand man of osama bin ladin , the organization 's leader , announced in a statement broadcast by the qatari aljazeera satellite channel that muslims and followers of al-qaeda must make themselves ready and mount operations against the embassies , interests , companies and employees of the united states , britain , australia and norway .
it should be noted that norway did not take part in the american coalition in the war against iraq . it also played a prominent role in bringing the palestinians and israelis to their peace agreement , known as the oslo accord , in the 1990s .
tibet sees rapid growth in private companies .
lasa 10 january ( xinhua ) the private economy of the tibet autonomous region in the southwest of china has seen rapid growth in recent years on account of the support of the central government , according to chow chin shio , director of the department of commerce and industry in the tibet region .
statistics from the region 's administration show that in 2003 tibet had 1823 registered private companies with a value of 3.8 billion yuan ( 459 million american dollars ) , an annual increase of 22.69% .
chow said that tibet had achieved a good mix between the development of private companies and the reemployment of workers made unemployed .
the official added that the autonomous region had encouraged unemployed nationals to begin their private commercial activity through preferential policies .
chow mentioned that these policies had expanded the field of private company business and had abolished specific restrictions imposed on investor specifications and the registered funding with which they start , which had allowed the tibetan private economy to prosper .
israeli killed and others wounded in armed attack in west bank .
gaza 13 january ( xinhua ) israeli broadcasting reported that an israeli settler was killed and two others suffered medium wounds in an ambush mounted by armed palestinians of a car driving near the basgat zaef settlement near the area of ramallah in the west bank .
the broadcaster said the operation took place in the area between the habarsa and post crossroads near the " talmunim " settlement bloc .
it explained that the armed palestinians opened fire on the vehicle and fled . one of the passengers received serious injuries as a consequence of which he died , whilst the driver of the car and another passenger suffered medium wounds .
following the operations many forces from the israeli army rushed to the scene and began to comb the area , in search of the perpetrators .
israeli estimates in the west bank suggest that the al-aqsa martyrs brigade , the military wing counted part of the fateh movement , was responsible for the operation .
in a related context , 200 armed palestinians from fateh demonstrated in protest at the attempt to assassinate their leader in the north of the west bank , zakaria zubaida . the brigades promised revenge .
france and bahrain demand formation of iraqi national government is speeded up .
riyadh 14 january ( xinhua ) a report from manama this evening states that france and bahrain have demanded that the formation of a national government in iraq to supervise elections comprising all sections of the iraqi people and preserving the unity and sovereignty of iraq must be speeded up .
this came in a joint press conference held by the bahraini foreign minister sheikh muhammad bin mubarak al khalifa and his visiting french counterpart dominic de villepin following their talks today in manama .
the bahrain foreign minister said that the two sides had agreed on the importance of a resumption to the peace process and the implementation of the road map by movement of the international group of four committee in this regard on the way to a just and comprehensive peace in the region .
for his part de villepin said that the french and bahrain sides had agreed that the situation in palestine at present had become pressing , and would lead to further struggle , and that the road map , which provides for the establishment of the palestinian state by the start of 2005 , must be activated
he added that the two sides had also discussed terrorism and the threat it presented to states and societies with agreement being reached to combat terrorism and counter it internationally .
de villepin arrived in manama this morning on a short visit to bahrain as part of his tour to a number of states of the region .
treatment of wastewater in peking .
peking 15 january ( xinhua ) the rate of treatment of wastewater in peking has increased from 5% to 56% in the period between 1990/2003 , an increase of 10% annually .
the first plant to treat wastewater was established and operated in peking in 1990 .
40 thousand cubic meters of wastewater were treated in that year .
peking invested in the construction of 7 new plants over the next 13 years .
in 2003 the volume of wastewater treated in peking reached 1.58 million cubic meters , 40 times more than in 1990 .
in 2004 projects to treat waste water in peking will focus on the areas surrounding the olympic village and the liang shui river , where 1.5 billion chinese yuan ( 181.378 million american dollars ) will be invested in the construction of 4 plants to treat wastewater , thereby increasing the capacity for treatment of wastewater by 30 thousand cubic meters per day or 10% .
samjhauta express train between india and pakistan reaches atari in india .
new delhi 15 january ( xinhua ) the samjhauta express train on the lahore - atari route with its twin green and yellow colors owned by pakistan railways reached atari in the northwest of india this afternoon . this represents a resumption of movement on the railways between the two neighbors , which was cut off two years ago , and opens a new page in relations between india and pakistan .
the train , which carried 65 passengers , arrived at atari railway station at 12:55 , according to a report by the indian press trust news agency .
the passengers from pakistan will be subject to an immigration inspection at atari before catching a train linking atari with new delhi later today .
according to the agency , the passengers climbed on the coach enthusiastically when it entered india .
the train , which was also known as the friendship train , left lahore at about nine am ( pakistan time ) .
the train travels between lahore and atari on mondays and thursdays .
the two states are currently resuming the railways , road and air links that were severed following the terrorist attack on the indian parliament in december 2001 .
japan extends mission of its peacekeeping forces in golan heights .
tokyo 16 january ( xinhua ) the japanese government decided today , friday , to extend the participation of japanese forces in the united nations peacekeeping mission in the golan heights , which are occupied by israel , following a resolution to continue the mission issued by the international security council .
the council of ministers extended the duration of the japanese mission for a further six months to end on the 30th of next september , according to the foreign ministry .
the ministry said that the international security council had , last december , extended the mission of the forces monitoring the united nations disengagement in the golan heights for a further six months ending on the 30th of next june .
the united nations has deployed forces to monitor the disengagement in the golan heights since 1974 to maintain the ceasefire between israel and syria .
the japanese forces have participated in the forces monitoring the disengagement since february 1996 .
telephone contact between powell and his kuwaiti counterpart .
kuwait 16 january ( xinhua ) kuwaiti foreign minister sheikh muhammad sabah al-salim al sabah received a telephone call this evening from his american counterpart colin powell concerning the american announcement to view kuwait a strategic ally of america outside the north atlantic alliance .
the kuwaiti foreign ministry statement reported that powell announced that the procedures for official implementation of this classification would begin shortly , noting that sheikh muhammad had expressed kuwait 's gratitude and appreciation at this classification .
elsewhere , chairman of the kuwait council of the nation foreign affairs committee muhammad jasim al-saqr welcomed the american announcement and described it as an important step towards completing special strategic relations for the interests of kuwait and its future and to preserve stability and security in the region .
al-saqr explained in a press statement distributed here this evening that kuwait 's special status with the united states would allow it to communicate the voice and hopes of the people of the region regarding the issues and problems they suffer from .
foreign minister : australian american trade agreement still faces major problems .
canberra 17 january ( xinhua ) australian foreign minister alexander downer said today , saturday , that negotiations with the united states on concluding a bilateral free trade agreement still faced problems .
he told sky news television , " there are still major obstacles to be overcome but we are optimistic about the possibility of overcoming them . "
negotiations are still taking place about the agreement , which was to have been completed by the start of last christmas . the major issues that have yet to be resolved include australia 's inclusion in the american agricultural market and permission for american media products to enter australia .
downer said , " in the end a bad agreement is not an agreement that we can sign . "
the foreign minister , who leaves on a foreign visit today , saturday , will visit los angeles to hold free trade talks with american officials .
he will then visit the middle east to discuss the peace process with regional leaders , including the israeli prime minister ariel sharon .
downer said that australia wants israel and the palestinians to return to the path of road map for peace in the middle east .
severe shortage in electricity supply in south china .
guangzhou 18 january ( xinhua ) the electricity supply in five provinces in south china will experience severe shortages in 2004 on account of the rapid rise in the demand for electricity arising from continuing economic growth .
from a working meeting of the southern company of the national electricity network held here recently the correspondent learnt that the early arrival of peak electricity consumption in five provinces in south china will constitute a major challenge for the safe working of the electricity network and meeting the electricity needs of local economies .
in view of this situation the company has drawn up a range of measures to reduce pressure on electricity supplies , including transmission of electricity from west china to the east .
the volume of electricity transferred to quangdong will reach 36.4 billion kilowatts , an annual increase of 46.7%
the company will also work to guide the electricity market by prices and will increase the electricity price in the peak season .
exhibition of ancient buddhist statues in hong kong .
hong kong ( xinhua ) an exhibition of ancient buddhist statues opened on saturday at hong kong university where , for the first time , about 50 buddhist statues and engraved tombstones dating back to the northern dynasty ( 386-550 ) and the sui - song dynasty ( 581-1279 ) are being exhibited .
these buddhist statues show the ancient history of the art of stone engravings in ancient chinese history and its magnificent and varied artistic forms .
the exhibits of tombstone engravings show the high level of the arts of calligraphy , engraving and sculpture in ancient chinese history .
scientists in hong kong said that these artistic works reflect the magnificent achievements of the stone engraving and sculpture arts in ancient chinese history . the exhibition also provides a rare opportunity for admirers of ancient chinese arts and culture in hong kong to enjoy these valuable historical , cultural and artistic works and meet the shortfall in historical documents for cultural and historical studies in hong kong .
malaysian prime minister visits philippines .
manila 18 january ( xinhua ) malaysian prime minister abdullah ahmad badawi is to carry out a two - day visit to the philippines , commencing on monday , with the aim of progressing bilateral relations between the two countries .
prime minister badawi is expected to hold talks with philippines president gloria macapagal concerning bilateral relations and the most recent developments in malaysia 's efforts to mediate in the peace talks between the philippines government and the moro islamic liberation front , according to the abs - cbn news station .
malaysia also agreed to host peace talks between the government and the moro islamic liberation front , the largest rebel group in the philippines , in kuala lumpur this month .
the united states , which has undertaken to provide diplomatic and financial support , will also have a role in the negotiations .
badawi flies to manila from laos where he is conducting a tour of southeast asia , during which he is announcing his outlooks .
badawi has become the fifth malaysian prime minister since its independence from britain in 1957 after mahathir mohamad stepped down in 2003 .
china and egypt to sign several agreements during visit of chinese president to egypt .
cairo 18 january ( xinhua ) china 's ambassador to egypt wu si keh held a press conference this evening , sunday , at the embassy in cairo during which he spoke about the visit to be conducted by chinese president hu jintao to egypt on the 29th of this january .
mr. wu said that the first visit of the chinese president to the region would begin in egypt on 29 january and end on the 1st of next february , as egypt is one of the most important states with ties to china in the region .
the chinese ambassador explained that during the visit a review of the strategic cooperation agreement between china and egypt would be conducted on the occasion of five years passing since it was signed . he noted that a number of agreements would be signed between the countries , including agreements in the economic and media sectors .
egyptian and foreign media operating in egypt attended the conference .
quangdong prevents import of used electronic and electrical appliances and household waste .
guangzhou 19 january ( xinhua ) the permanent committee of the local people 's council in the province of quangdong ( south china ) approved a " list for protection and treatment of environmental pollution arising from solid waste for the province of quangdong " some days ago .
the list , which comes into effect on 1 may , provides for the prohibition of the management and use of electronic and electrical appliance and prevents the entry of household waste to the province from abroad or from other provinces , autonomous regions and central municipalities .
an official for the environment protection department in the province said the adoption of this list by the quangdong province aimed to limit the increase in environmental pollution arising from solid waste .
he added that household waste required massive sums and advanced technology for treatment in view of its size and complexity and could lead to the return of pollution .
egyptian communications company launches new television station in iraq .
cairo 21 january ( xinhua ) nagib sawiras , an official from the egyptian investment company orascom telecom , stated here today , wednesday , that within the next two months broadcasts would begin of a new television company in iraq owned by the company . it will broadcast programs in different economic , political and varied sectors .
in press statements sawiras said the he had obtained from the interim ruling council in iraq the necessary approval to set up this station , which will be given the name " hawa " . he noted that several projects would be set up in iraq within the framework of reconstruction .
egypt is one of the states allowed by the united states to participate in the reconstruction of iraq , the value of which is estimated at 18.6 billion dollars . in this context , the egyptian company working in the communications sector orascom telecom has won contracts to rebuild the mobile phone network in baghdad .
indonesia : australia 's participation in american missile defense program helps establish security in region .
jakarta 21 january ( xinhua ) indonesian armed forced said today , wednesday , that the involvement of australia in the american missile defense system could help establish security in the region .
the general commander of the indonesian armed forces general endriartono sutarto stated , " we could benefit from it in establishing regional stability . "
he explained this by saying that against the background of good cooperation australia 's involvement could be an advantage more than a security threat .
the general said that bilateral military cooperation was one way to bring advantages to both sides .
spokesman for the indonesian foreign ministry marty natalegawa has previously stated that indonesia is anxious at the participation of australia in the american missile defense program , saying that such participation would not help establish regional security and could provoke an arms race in the region .
world bank encourages russia to participate in restructuring iraqi loans .
moscow 21 january ( xinhua ) the interfax news agency reported that james wolfensohn , the visiting president of the world bank , called on russia today to take part in the restructuring of iraqi debts , saying that it would be a positive step .
wolfensohn , who arrived here yesterday on a two - day working visit to russia , said that russian president vladimir putin recently met with american presidential envoy james baker , who has been charged with settling iraq 's debts of 120 billion dollars .
the president of the world bank also praised russia for adopting a constructive manner in reducing the burden of debt for some developing countries .
during his meeting with wolfensohn , putin said that russia had dropped debts totaling more than 30 billion dollars during the previous five years .
putin also gave an undertaking yesterday that russia would continue to drop the debts of the poorest countries in the world .
officials in an iraqi delegation that visited russia last december had said that moscow had promised to drop some of iraq 's debts .
they said that iraq 's debts to russia , totaling 8 billion dollars , would be reduced to 3.5 billion dollars and the remainder would be restructured with the paris club . however , there has been no confirmation from the russian authorities to date .
trade between fujian and taiwan sees small increase in 2003 .
futchu 22 january ( xinhua ) the eastern province of fujian , which faces taiwan across the taiwan straits , witnessed a rapid increase in its exports to taiwan in 2003 , whilst the volume of trade between the two sides saw a slow increase compared with the previous year .
the total volume of trade between fujian and taiwan reached 3.57 billion american dollars last year , an increase of 6.5% in comparison with 2002 , according to the commercial authorities in the province .
fujian represents a key partner on the mainland with the island province and is the only one on the mainland to have a direct shipping link with taiwan from xiamen , the closest city on the mainland to taiwan , to quemoy island in taiwan .
fujian 's total revenue from taiwan reached 3.05 billion american dollars last year , an increase of 4.54% compared to 2002 , with exports reaching 519 million american dollars , an increase of 19.78% .
the province recorded a trade deficit of 2.53 billion american dollars with taiwan in 2003 , an increase of 1.89% compared to the previous year .
it should be noted that more than 80% of taiwanese are descended from the people of south fujian , with whom they share the same culture and language .
iraqi police attacked west of baghdad .
baghdad 22 january ( xinhua ) the iraqi police announced today , thursday , that unknown armed men attacked iraqi policemen in the town of al-falujah , west of baghdad , and killed several of them according to a report by the al-arabia satellite channel .
the channel quoted an officer in the iraqi police as saying , " there was an attack on the iraqi police which left several of them dead . " he added that the attack took place on the highway between the town of al-falujah and al-rumadi west of baghdad .
there was no other information about the incident .
in a separate incident , the qatari satellite channel aljazeera reported today , thursday , that two iraqi security guards were killed and another wounded as a result of gunfire on wednesday night after members of an american patrol became suspicious of movements in a car showroom in the town of al-falujah , west of baghdad .
the channel said that the effects of the gunfire were apparent on the vehicles of the showroom , the glass of which was smashed . the iraqi police rushed to the scene to investigate it .
death of person in thailand suspected of catching bird flu .
bangkok 23 january ( xinhua ) thai minister of health sudarat keyuraphan said that a thai suspected of catching bird flu died on friday night .
in a discussion with the local itv television the minister said that a person had died in the province of tchatchonjsao this evening . it has not yet been established whether bird flu was the cause of the death .
the man , a butcher in his fifties , was one of the sick suspected of catching bird flu . the laboratory investigation has not yet confirmed whether he had the disease or not .
thailand confirmed yesterday afternoon , friday , that two children showing symptoms of lung infections were infected with bird flu . virus h5n1 , which causes the outbreak , has been found in some chicken farms in central thailand .
sumtchai birabakorn , who is conducting the work of the world health organization representative with thailand told the xinhua news agency that this was the first time that bird flu had been transmitted between human beings and chickens .
in the event that it is confirmed that the death was caused by bird flu this person will become the first person to be killed by the disease in thailand .
the disease killed five people in vietnam .
control of breach of reservoir dam in north west china .
oromtchi 23 january ( xinhua ) more than two thousand army , armed police and militia personnel have , over the last two days , restored a 60 meter breach in a reservoir dam in the autonomous region of xinjiang of the wigor national group in south west china .
tchang tching , commander of the production and construction authority in xinjiang said that by ten o ' clock this evening the flow of water from the reservoir known by the name " payi " or " 1st of august " had slowed to 30 cubic meters per second and the level of water stored in the reservoir had fallen to 2.4 meters .
tchang said , " it was possible to take control of the situation . "
the breach in the dam happened on wednesday night , the evening of the traditional chinese new lunar year .
now , all of the population at risk , who numbered 13800 people , have been evacuated and given refuge .
there have been no reports about victims in spite of the fact that the water submerged eight companies of the xinjiang corporation
the reservoir , it should be mentioned , was built in 1957 with a storage capacity of 30 million cubic meters .
the central state committee for control of floods and rescue from drought has arrived in the area , which has been struck by floods .
jordanian monarch returns to amman from davos .
amman 24 january ( xinhua ) jordanian monarch king abdallah ii returned this evening , saturday , to amman after taking part in the meetings of the international economic forum in davos .
the jordanian monarch gave a political address to the forum in which he focused on the necessity of all sectors in the arab world dealing with issues such as government that responds to the aspirations of its people and adopts transparency , an educational system dedicated to the production of excellence and an active private system that can exploit the massive potential of the region .
the jordanian monarch held several meetings with a number of leaders and officials on the fringes of the forum .
in a meeting for governors of the health care sector , he expressed his concern to attract international companies to invest in the jordanian pharmaceutical industry , in order to help jordanian pharmaceutical companies acquire scientific and technical knowledge and innovation , or by jordanian companies assisting in the manufacture of some of the products of the international pharmaceutical companies .
united states lifts tuna fish ban imposed on el salvador .
mexico city 24 january ( xinhua ) the united states has lifted a ban on the import of tuna fish , which it imposed in 1994 on el salvador , after reports confirmed that the country , which lies in central america , had stopped using fishing nets dangerous to dolphins .
reports received here on saturday state that the united states is persuaded that el salvador has fulfilled the requirements to protect dolphins in the pacific ocean and respect the laws of the tropical tuna fish committee between the two americas .
douglas parsley , american ambassador to el salvador , announced the end of the ban on the import of tuna fish , adding that this " will provide new commercial opportunities for companies specializing in this industry " .
the united states imports tuna fish only from mexico , ecuador and el salvador , the volume of the annual production of which is 20 thousand tones .
philippine army rejects invitation to take over government .
manila 25 january ( xinhua ) the philippine armed forces today , sunday , rejected an invitation presented by a group that the army temporarily take over the command of government on account of the anticipated crisis .
director of the public media office of the philippine armed forces lt. col . daniel losiro said that the measure proposed by the citizens national crisis committee , which says that it represents a broad section of society , violates the country 's constitution .
losiro said , " the philippine armed forces will not consider this proposal .
this proposal urges the soldiers to overthrow the government , which represents a breach of the constitution . "
in an open letter he said that the group had urged the chief of staff of the philippine armed forces general narsiso apaye to take over the affairs of government because those hoping to win the presidency ( in the may elections ) and the political parties had failed to discuss the genuine and critical programs that tear the nation apart . "
the group also put forward an urgent program implementation of which the philippine armed forces could discuss during the proposed take over .
losiro said that the military institution , which comprises 113 thousand soldiers , would continue to support the constitutional government and would abide by the provisions set out in the constitution .
he called on the group to assist the army remain distant from any policies .
israeli sources think probable washington 's approval of disengagement plan .
gaza 25 january ( xinhua ) political sources in israel think it probable that the united states of america will agree to israel 's unilateral plan to disengage from the palestinians in the west bank .
american radio " sawa " reported today , sunday , quoting these sources , said that the united states might agree to implement this plan as a unilateral phase on the part of israel in implementation of the american road map . it added that there was an agreement of views between israel and the united states that palestinian prime minister ahmad qurei ( abu al-ala ) would not be able to resume talks with israel and israel would therefore have to find other ways to break the political stalemate on the palestinian - israeli tract .
on the same level , sources in the office of israeli prime minister ariel sharon said that israel would intensify the activities of the special team headed by major general jiura ailin to complete the plan for a unilateral separation in the west bank .
the sources added that sharon would present this plan to american president george bush in their meeting to be held in washington next february .
iraqi bank of commerce collects export guarantees for reconstruction companies .
baghdad 25 january ( xinhua ) the iraqi bank of commerce , set up by the united states , has acquired two billion four hundred million american dollars in export guarantees for companies wishing to conclude deals as part of the framework for reconstructing iraq .
the al-arabia news channel reported this evening , sunday , that the bank had issued about one and thirty letters of guarantee to a value of three hundred million dollars . the bank had also received requests from seventeen international bodies for export credits .
the al-arabia channel noted that a group of banks have offered export credit with reserves of about five billion dollars .
it should be mentioned that the iraqi bank of commerce , which was set up by an international consortium led by american firm jp morgan in july 2003 , was founded with capital of 100 million dollars to provide funding for commercial deals and to issue letters of credit in post - war iraq for the benefit of private and public sectors .
chinese economic and financial figures for week ( first and final addition ) .
chinese investments in the property sector reached 828.5 billion yuan ( about 100.18 billion american dollars ) in the period from january to february 2003 , an annual increase of 32.5% .
china imported 14.447 billion american dollars of car products in 2003 , an annual increase of 84% , representing a record .
china 's revenue from local and international tourism is expected to reach 487.4 billion yuan ( about 58.93 billion american dollars ) in 2003 , a fall of 12.4% but higher than expected .
four chinese financial capital management companies treated 37.509 billion yuan ( about 61.59 billion american dollars ) of inactive assets by the end of 2003 . financial imports in cash reached 99.41 billion yuan ( about 12.02 billion american dollars ) , taking up 19.52% of the total inactive assets treated in phases .
new reserve in shangli oil field exceeds 100 million tones .
jinan 28 january ( xinhua ) the xinhua agent recently learnt from the shangli oil field in the shandong province located in east china that recently confirmed reserve of oil in the field totals 113.01 million tones in 2003 . this raises the confirmed reserve of oil in this old field by 100 million tones per year for a continuous period of 21 years .
an official in the field said that this new reserve included 356.18 million tones suitable for immediate extraction .
in addition , scientists at the field discovered more than 200 million tones of unconfirmed reserve last year .
the official added that a large amount of sophisticated and new technology was used in the works to develop the field last year , which led to the extraction of more high - density oil and to the discovery of easily extractable oil reserve .
ban on slaughtering chickens in peking markets .
peking 28 january ( xinhua ) the slaughter of chickens and the sale of non - inspected meat and chicken products were banned in peking today , wednesday , as part of an emergency step taken by the local government to secure the capital against the spread of the bird flu virus to it .
it was confirmed yesterday , tuesday , that the virus was the cause of the death of ducks in the autonomous region of quangshi of the tchiang national group in south china .
lio jian , deputy director of the office of trade and industry in peking municipality , announced here today , wednesday , stricter control and inspection measures in order to prevent the entry of poultry products from other locales to peking .
lio said that the food safety office of peking municipality must be informed immediately in the event of a case of bird flu and that anyone delaying notification would be severely punished .
statistics issued by the local government show that there are 139 chicken farms , 63 markets , 36 supermarkets and 31 chicken slaughterhouses in peking .
no poultry products arriving from countries infected by the bird flu disease , such as the republic of korea , vietnam , japan and thailand , have yet been found in the local markets .
the operations to inspect the chicken products available in peking during the spring holiday demonstrate that these products are free from bird flu and are safe to consume , according to an official in the food safety office .
end of joint military maneuvers between yemen and the united states .
sanaa 28 january ( xinhua ) yemeni sources reported that units of the yemeni and american coastguard ended joint military maneuvers in the gulf of aden today , wednesday .
the sources said that these joint military maneuvers between yemen and the united states included training in countering terrorist operations that could target ships . however , they did not given any details about the maneuvers .
the sources noted that yemen will , at the beginning of next march , receive eight coastguard vessels after a yemeni crew completed training on them in the united states last month as part of the yemeni plan which aims to consolidate coastguard operations and prevent penetration operations via it from neighboring countries .
the united states , it is worth noting , is linked to yemen by an anti - terrorist agreement and is providing the assistance necessary for yemen to form an effective coastguard to protect the yemeni coasts , which extend for 2500 km from its borders with the sultanate of oman on the arabian sea to the saudi borders on the red sea .
blair accepts hutton report in full .
london 28 january ( xinhua ) british prime minister tony blair said today , wednesday , that he accepted the report of lord hutton , which cleared him of any involvement in the suicide of weapons expert david kelly last year .
following publication of the results of lord hutton 's report , blair told parliament , " the claims that i or any other person willfully lied to this house and misled the country by falsifying intelligence information about weapons of mass destruction are themselves lies . "
the prime minister said that he was " very satisfied " with brian hutton , the senior british judge who published the results of his investigations into kelly 's death an hour ago .
amidst warm applause by members of the labor party , to which he belongs , blair said , " the report represents an exceptionally comprehensive , detailed and clear document and leaves no room for doubt or interpretation . "
we accept this report in full . "
he confirmed , " there was no dishonest strategy to leak the name of dr kelly . "
blair called on all those who had accused him of lying on the iraq issue to withdraw their allegations .
blair said , " i simply ask that those who made this allegation and repeated it over all these months withdraw it now frankly , clearly and fully . "
zimbabwe urged to consolidate relations with china .
harare 28 january ( xinhua ) a zimbabwean official stressed here today the importance of his country exploiting the massive potential of the chinese market in order to reduce the severity of the sanctions imposed by western states on zimbabwe .
savior kasukuwere , chairman of the parliamentary defense and internal affairs committee , made this statement whilst presenting a report to parliament about the visit made by a delegation from his committee to china .
kasukuwere said , " china provides an opportunity for zimbabwe to establish cooperation with a friendly state prepared to provide assistance . "
giles mutsekwa , member of parliament for the mutare north area , from the opposition movement for democratic change undertook a visit with kasukuwere to china between the 22 and 27th of last october .
there is still the potential to set up joint companies to provide more opportunities to transfer technology and added value to zimbabwean products , according to the official .
zimbabwe and china , it should be noted , enjoy strong relations that go back to the days of the struggle for liberation in the african state .
return of 2500 afghan refugees to their country this year .
kabul 29 january ( xinhua ) manuel de almeida e silva , spokesman for the united nations , said here today that 2500 afghan refugees from eight states , in particular iran , had returned to their country to date in 2004 .
in a press conference he said that the refugees , who include about one thousand survivors from the destructive earthquake that hit the city of bam in eastern iran , returned to afghanistan with the help of the united nations refugee agency .
the spokesman said , " the refugee agency will continue to help afghans who survived the bam earthquake to return as long as they wish to return " . he added that the agency had provided essential food and full heating to those arriving at the transit center in herat .
elsewhere , 50 refugees from seven other states returned with the help of the agency .
more than 2.2 million afghan refugees have returned to their country since the start of the refugee return operation in 2002 , which is facilitated by the agency . more than 252 thousand other refugees returned from iran over the same period .
disappointment in negev prison after return of 43 palestinian prisoners to prison .
gaza 29 january ( xinhua ) tens of palestinian detainees experienced disappointment after the israeli prisons authority announced that it was removing the names of 37 palestinian prisoners in the desert prison of negev , southern israel , from the list of those released today , thursday .
a number of palestinian prisoners said that the prisons authority yesterday returned 37 prisoners whom it had decided to release today . 16 other prisoners were also returned . no reasons were given for the removal of the names .
in a telephone contact with the new chinese news agency ( xinhua ) palestinian detainee hani abu nahl said that the conditions of the palestinian detainees were very difficult after the israeli prison authorities released a small number of detainees as part of the exchange deal .
abu nahl said , " the prison authorities brought us out in preparation to release us but they returned me and , with me , 42 detainees , and informed us that our names had been taken off the list of those released . "
detainee abdallah anjas from ramallah said , " the israeli prison guards want to play with the nerves of the detainees , some of whom wept at the difficult conditions they have experienced , confirming that most of those released had short sentences and only had a short time to serve . "
